TY  - JOUR
TI  - A Transformation Used to Circumvent the Problem of Autocorrelation
AU  - Kadiyala, Koteswara Rao
AB  - [In this paper it is shown that, when the disturbances <tex-math>$\varepsilon _{t}=y_{t}-\Sigma _{j=1}^{k}x_{tj}\beta _{j}$</tex-math> in a regression model follow a first order autoregressive process with the parameter ρ generating the process, there exist cases where the classical least squares regression analysis as applied to the n — 1 observations: <tex-math>$y_{t}-\rho y_{t-1},x_{tj}-\rho x_{t-1,j}$</tex-math> (j = 1, 2,..., k; t = 2,..., n), is less efficient than the classical least squares regression analysis as applied to the original n observations: <tex-math>$y_{t},x_{tj}(t=1,...,n)$</tex-math>. It is shown that the efficiency of the former relative to the latter could be arbitrarily close to zero in some cases.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan., 1968
